case_circumstances: On 01/03/16 at 0230 hours another transient in the encampment was checking on people, as he states that he usually does every night, when he found the decedent unresponsive and contacted 911 from his cell phone.  Deputies and paramedics arrived and death was determined without intervention at 0237 hours.  Paramedics report that they recognize the decedent as someone whom they have had constant contact with but did not provide Deputies with her name or any identifying information.  They report a history of heavy alcohol abuse.  Witnesses report that they saw the decedent sitting on a nearby milk crate the day before (01/02/16) at 1530 hours at which time she was witnessed falling forward and hitting her head on the sidewalk while heavily intoxicated.  She was last known alive at 2130 hours when she was seen lying down to go to sleep on the sidewalk.
